snippet.title: Stoveplay: Brandish 3: Spirit of Balcan (PC-98) Part 1: Introduction, Tantoll
snippet.description:
I'm still here. I had a busy summer.
 
The NEC PC-9800 (zeroes optional) is the younger, stronger brother of the PC-8800, with a more powerful everything. It also showed me the true meaning of dithering. What a machine.

In Brandish you step and/or pull on switches and crawl through the dungo.

(Note: I decided I have standards after all and restarted this playthrough from the very beginning. The sound quality was bugging me and I made too many recording goofs.)
